\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 You were about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11933455\charrsid6102048 16}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  years old in 1900 were you? Can you tell me your birthday' 19}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \super\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  of Aug
ust but I couldn't tell you the year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. J. 1884.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 So if you were born in 1884 you were about 16 years old in 1900. What were you doing when you were 16 years old. Were you in service?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 In domestic service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Could you tell me about your first place that you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 A schoolmaster at the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Blue}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8405883\charrsid6102048 coat{\*\xmlclose} }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Colchester
{\*\xmlclose}. They only kept a maid but the had a charwoman in your see. It wasn't a big house of course and I only stayed there a couple of years. I went into domestic service in a gentleman's service he was chaplain to the forces in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Colchester{\*\xmlclose}. I remained there until they went away. They were only stationed there for a length of time and that was that. Shall I tell you about the place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 About you first place. Were you a housemaid? What were you called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, no! I was just a maid to help the lady she did work. I was just a maid. They kept }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8405883\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  little girls. They had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8405883\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
 little girls at school and the lady did the work with a charwoman in. I lived in as a maid you see and did all the little small work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What would you have called yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, a general maid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And can you tell me what your first pay was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 When I first went into service }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11933455\charrsid6102048 1/6d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 How old were you in your first job. Was it straight after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 About }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8405883\charrsid6102048 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
teen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And were you paid by the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, monthly. Every month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And did you get any other payment in kind if you know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No. But if they had a visitor I used to get what they called a tip.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And how much would that be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh a shilling - sometimes }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11933455\charrsid6102048 1/6d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 How often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, not very often. Twice a year or something like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 So it didn't make a very big difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What about clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, no. Not there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And did you have all your meals there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did they provide you with uniform. Did you wear a uniform?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Print frocks in the morning and black in the afternoon with white aprons and a cap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And in the morning did you wear a cap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And what was it like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, just a little white muslin we thought they were smart in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did you say that your employer provided you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, no. We had to provide that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 So when you went to your first job did you but your uniform before you came to her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Mother bought it. Of course we didn't have just what the ladies always wanted. Mothers couldn't afford it. We just had our print frocks and a black frock in the afternoon and a cap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Would the lady then tell your mother? Did the lady meet your mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mother used to come and see us occasionally mother did. Yes. But if they were not satisfied with us they'd soon pack us off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 How did you get that first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 We used to hear of it through friends. In {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Colchester{\*\xmlclose}
 that was. Or you probable might see it in the paper advertised. Maid wanted. I believe we did see that in the paper. I'm not sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And then what would you do? What would be the next step. Did you go to her house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Call on her. Interview.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And did she ask you a lot of questions? Can you remember it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No. Not really a lot. There was just about an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11933455\charrsid6102048 8}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  roomed house and a kitchen. And it was one of those houses. In those days there was no bathroom.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 The schoolmaster's house had no bathroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No bathroom. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Can you describe to me what your duties were. Imagine - from when you got up in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 The first thing light the kitchen fire and put the water on for breakfast and water for carrying up into the bedrooms for 
their washing: great big copper jugs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What time would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 About half past }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11933455\charrsid6102048 7}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 . Breakfast at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11933455\charrsid6102048 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}
{\xmlattrvalue 8}}}8}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  o'clock{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Was that your breakfast or theirs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well their breakfast really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 When did you have your breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well I'd had my breakfast with the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11933455\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  little girls in the kitchen often enough before they went to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 You ate with them and give them their breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What did they have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Porridge and never any meat for breakfast. Even the schoolm
aster didn't have meat. Bread and butter and caster sugar. Always. Never knew them to have anything else for breakfast. Not in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And after that what would you do next?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 After breakfast and they'd gone off t
o school we used to clear the table, wash up and then go upstairs and the lady of the house - we made the beds together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 How many would there be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. and Mrs. Brown's bedroom. The girl's bedroom. Only }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11933455\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 . And then my own. I used to do my own bedroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And after you'd made the beds then what.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Well there was the work cut out for each day. Monday there was odd jobs and bits of washing. In the ordinary round the linen went to the laundry. We used to do the small tea cloths and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11933455\charrsid6102048 towels
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  and thi
ngs like that and the little girls things. We used to do that on a Monday. Tuesday we used to turn out one bedroom. Wednesday another bedroom. And Thursday - I'm not sure whether it was my bedroom. I believe it was my bedroom on the Thursday and then Frid
ay was the drawing room. I can still see the furniture in that drawing room. He was a schoolmaster by day and he had a Botany Class in the evening.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Turning out the rooms and washing. That was morning work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 That was morning work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What time would you finish that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Always finished that before dinner. They had mid-day dinner. No late dinner. Just a plain dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And what part did you play in preparing the dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Not any. Only the vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Who cooked the dinner in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, the lady used to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11933455\charrsid6102048  superintend.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6102048  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 I didn't do it on my own then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did she do any actual cooking herself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, yes. She'd make a pudding and I'd have an eye to the joint and I'd by busy after the other work. She used to make cakes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Who had dinner first or did you eat at the same time as she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 We all had it together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Can you describe to me what it was like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well the main dinner was ... on a Saturday it was just a roast beef. And }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11933455\charrsid6102048 
2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  vegetables and sometimes a Yorkshire pudding; and after that the sweet like }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11933455\charrsid6102048 blancmange}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  and fruit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Any cheese.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, not at that meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Was there a cloth on the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, yes. A big white table cloth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And what sort of cutlery and crockery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Silver in those days. I had to clean that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And side plates and glasses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No only tumblers when I lived there. Tumblers and a jug of water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Anything else. Can you picture it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 A cruet. A cruet used to stand in the centre of the table.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 You say you did the washing up all on your own. What did you wash up in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 A big enamel bowl and drained them in another bowl and them dry them and put them all away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did you have soap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, not soap. A little washing soda.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Then did you dry them up with a cloth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And what did you do after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 I used to do a little bit of knitting and crocheting in those days - for myself. Nothing for the lady. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And where would you do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And did you do any mending?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did the lady do the mending.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, she did all the mending. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Was anything sent out in the way of sewing? Sent out of the house. Did anyone come and do sewing or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 They used to have friends call to see them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And how often did the laundry go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Once a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Can you tell me what the little girls were like. What sort of children were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Do you want to know their names?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 They were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11933455\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  very nice little children. The eldest girl's name was Ina and the second one was Vera. They both went to a private school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What was the school called.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well I couldn't tell you. They were only babies then at the time they were only young children and I believe it was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11933455\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  ladies at a school in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Colchester{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Were they happy there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, yes I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And how did you get on with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Had they got good manners.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Very. Very well behaved. If not they'd got their Dad ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What did they call you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well if I tell you what they called me. It's very funny. 'Pally'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And what did you call them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 I used to call them 'Ina' and 'Vera'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 You say you changed your clothes in the afternoon. Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Af
ter dinner - after the washing up I'd change. We were suppose to look a little bit 'smarter' when we went to the door to open it if anyone called you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And did people call.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, people ....well of course they were not what we'd call ...well th
ere is a name I don't quite know how to put it. They were not wealthy people. Just ordinary people. And people would call - perhaps another schoolmaster's wife, in the same station in life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And what would you do then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 I'd answer the door and if the lady was there they used to come in and have a chat and they used to let themselves out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And while they were there what were you doing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What I liked in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What sort of things would you do in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well .... I'd do a bit of sewing or something of my own. Knitting or that for myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did you (something I can't hear but she at the interview misheard anyway)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, no garden. I had to get the tea ready for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11933455\charrsid6102048 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 17}}}5}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  o'clock{\*\xmlclose}
. Lay the tea in the dining room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What would they have for tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Just bread and butter and jam and cakes. And the tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did the lady help get the tea ready?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What time would the callers leave?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 In the afternoon between }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11933455\charrsid6102048 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11933455\charrsid6102048 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  or so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 They'd stop coming by then would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, yes or just after }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6258416\charrsid6102048 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And what would happen then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Well, I was in the kitchen as usual and the lady of the house she was in her own drawing room if she wasn't out for a walk. She'd probably go and meet the children from school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What time did they come out of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6258416\charrsid6102048 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}
{\xmlattrvalue 16}}}4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6258416\charrsid6102048 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 'clock{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And then would you all have tea together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No. I and the children had tea in the kitchen and the others had it in the dining room. They liked their tea with me they could do mor
e as they liked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And while you had yours in the kitchen where was their mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 In the dining room having her tea with her husband.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 He came home then early did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6258416\charrsid6102048 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}
{\xmlattrvalue 16}}}4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  o'clock{\*\xmlclose}. Then he'd go back to classes in the evening occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 After you'd had your tea with the girls what happened then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 They used to like me to read to them. And they went to bed between {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 19}}}half past }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6258416\charrsid6102048 7}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 {\*\xmlclose} and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6258416\charrsid6102048 8}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did you supervise their bedtime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 They used to go upstairs and I used to see them into bed
 and after that their mother used to see they were alright. I saw they were in bed together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Do you think they spent more time with you or with their mother in the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well I don't really ... I don't know - they used to spend their evenings with me. Of course during the day they were at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 They only ate their mid-day dinner with their mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, that's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did she ever put them to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No. I don't know that she ever did. Their Mum and Dad always go up after they were in bed.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Used they to say prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, they used to say their prayers too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did anyone hear their prayers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 I think they used to say them aloud.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 To you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 To me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Not to their mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And when you read to them was it everyday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Well, not every - it just depends. If they were home after school in the evenings perhaps they would like me to have a game with them or perhaps do some writing. Just something to interest them not interest me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 How old were they when you first went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6258416\charrsid6102048  Ina}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6258416\charrsid6102048 8}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  and Vera would be }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6258416\charrsid6102048 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And how old were they when you left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well I don't quite know ... well I could say because I was only there }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6258416\charrsid6102048 2}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  years. I stayed a year and left and then they asked me back again. So I had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6258416\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  years there really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 So they would have been about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6258416\charrsid6102048 10 and 6 when you left }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did their mother ever read to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 I don't know; I really don't know. When they were in the dining room with their Mum and Dad I didn't quite know what they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What happened at weekends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mum and Dad always took them a long country walk in the afternoon and I went with them. I had to go with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did you enjoy that yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No. No, I didn't. They liked me to go with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 The children did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Yes. But in the holidays they'd take them out for a long walk and then they'd make some arrangement - somewhere where they knew us - some big house in the country we'd call there and have tea. They had to pay for this tea, just to give
 the children a treat.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 How often were you allowed time on your own to go out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well - I think about one evening a week. And Sundays. Yes, I'd go out Sunday evenings. I had a sister in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
place}}Colchester{\*\xmlclose} so we used to arrange to meet each other you see - we went out together you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Was it always the same evening every week or could you chop and change.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No. It was generally Wednesdays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did you ever have a whole day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No. I don't think I did. I think I used to go home for a day about once a month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 On a Sunday was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No. it wasn't always on a Sunday on a weekday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did you ever get a whole weekend day off or a half-day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No. We used to get a little holiday when it was holiday time at the schools.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 How long was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Perhaps a week or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8405883\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  while they were away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And did they pay you your wages then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 In the holiday - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Can you tell me how you felt about your first job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, I didn't like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 It didn't seem home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Were you lonely?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Well, yes. Sometimes. Yes, sometimes I felt lonely and thought I'd rather be at home with mother but of course mother and father couldn't afford to keep us at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Were you homesick?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 I believe I was sometimes. I think I was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And the actual work and being with the children how did you feel about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well it was company, and I liked the children and we got really fond of each other
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And what about the lady you worked for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, she was particularly kind. She was very kind indeed.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 So it wasn't a had place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No. it wasn't a bad place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Was she considerate? If you were tired ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, yes, she was very considerate. I liked her very much. I didn't like Mr. Brown.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What was he like then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 He was very strict. Very strict with the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Too strict?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Too strict I thought. Yes, too strict.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And how was he with you? Was he friendly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, yes. But he was the sort of gentleman that I wouldn't take to. Of course, he was a s
choolmaster and had a class of boys and I expect he had to be strict with them too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Can you think of anything about that first place that struck you at the time. The change say from your own home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well one thing I had a nice bedroom to myself - nothing elaborate but ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 You liked that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, I liked that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What about the way the family was. You know the relationship between the mother and the children. Did that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11933455\charrsid6102048 strike}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  you as funny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, they were very nice to each other. Very nice indeed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
I wondered if it would strike you as strange - as it might perhaps strike people nowadays that the mother didn't spend more time with her own children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, no. She was particularly fond of the children and of course as I say they w
ent to school and she only saw them at meal times till they come home in the evening for tea you see. She was with them a bit and always went to see them after they got into bed. No, they were a very friendly family - very friendly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And were you pleased to eat with them as one of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What about the next place, the gentleman's house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, I was just thinking where I did go from there. As a matter of fact I had more places in domestic service than many girls w
ould because I went with military people and they stayed in a place for so long. Now for instance, I was with one family who was chaplain to the Forces and they were very nice people. Chaplain, a sort of minister - clergyman; don't they call them a chapla
in.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 That's right, to the troops.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
To the troops, yes. They were there - his name was the Rev. Murphy and it was a lady recommended me to go there, she knew they wanted a maid and she spoke to me about it and she thought I would be happy. They wer
e very nice people, indeed. But I was only there a year and a half 'cos they went away from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Colchester{\*\xmlclose} to Nova ... Is there a place called {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}Nova Scotia{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 That's right, in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Canada{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, that's it, yes. And I was really sorry 'cos they were very nice
 people. And that's where I saw my first sovereign. A golden sovereign. Mrs. Murphy came into the kitchen one morning and she called me Alice - my Christian name - and I can see her now if you understand what I mean. Of course, the old people, we can look
 back and see. And she held it up like this and she said, '{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Alice{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, look'. And I was in the scullery - kitchen led into the scullery, what we used to call a scullery, where the washing up was done - and she laid it on what we call a dresser, I wonder if you know what I mean, where they kept the dinner services.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 People do still have them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Yes, that's right, yes. Well, she laid it on there and this is just what she said. She said 'you've given us every satisfaction', she said, 'we've very pleased with
 you', she said - and what did she say, did she say 'the Reverend Matthew', or did she say 'the master'? That I wouldn't be so sure about. She said 'and we're raising your wages'. I was getting }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1710819 \'a3}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6258416\charrsid6102048 10 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  year then, and that meant }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1710819 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 12 a year. Only 5/- a week then, was it, see. That was right, wasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
And this was a sovereign, the first sovereign I ever had of my own. But the were very nice people, but they went away - I think I was there about a year and a half and they went away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 So she was showing you that they were raising you to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1710819 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 1 a month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, that's right, yes. 5/- a week it would be. And I was only getting }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1710819 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6258416\charrsid6102048 10 a year. That}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6102048  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 was 16/8 in the month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, not much, is it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 It wasn't much. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11933455\charrsid6102048 But it was really wonderful, you
 know, we ... and there was 2 daughters there and they had a French governess. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
They didn't go to school, they were kept - they had a school room and a French governess. She was particularly kind, but she had rather a hard time with the girls. But I always remember these }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6258416\charrsid6102048 
2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  girls, one was Vio}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6258416\charrsid6102048 let and the other one was Norma}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
. And they were dressed ever so plain, of course they were. Exceptionally clean, well, they had to have baths every day. And their school room was just an ordinary room, perhaps no bigger th
an this, where they had their lessons and they'd got music in there, a piano, I think. And one thing they'd got which I always remember was a huge rocking horse. And the eldest girl was 14 and the younger one, Norma, I should think she was about 12, but e
v
ery morning those girls would get on to the rocking horse in their turn and sing. Sing a bit of a song out of their song books and away they'd go. Anyway, I used to like to hear it. We could hear it down in the kitchen or in the dining room, you know, and
 they were very nice girls. And when I'd been home - I used to get home for a day there, - she'd come out into the kitchen the next day, the girl would and she'd say to me, 'Well, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City
}}Alice{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, have you had a nice day out? How's your father and mother?' And they w
ere particularly nice. Well then, after they got away I had a particularly nice letter from them, very nice letter indeed, to say that if I wanted a reference she would be only too pleased to give it to me, give anyone a reference for And I'm afraid I'm b
l
owing me own trumpet but it's perfectly true what I'm telling you. And she was so sorry to have to tell me that the Reverend Murphy was riding his horse and threw him off and killed him. He was very fond of horses. He used to go for a ride every morning, 
they used to keep up amongst the troops, you see. So that was the end that I knew of them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 How did you feel when you heard that news?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, I felt very sorry because they were such nice people. Very nice people indeed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Can I just ask you one question? How old were these girls when you were then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, well, Vi, the eldest one, she'd be 15, and Norma, she'd be about 12.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did you have to do anything for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, no, no. They see after themselves. The governess - she had her own 
bedroom, of course. And the governess, the Rev. Murphy and his wife and the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8405883\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
 girls, they all had dinner in the dining room. We had it in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And did she have any other maids, or anyone to help her in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 She used to have a help in. She used to have a help in daily }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6258416\charrsid6102048 2 or 3}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  days a week and the Rev. Murphy had what they call - what did they call then
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 A batman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 That's right, yes. Used to come up and brush his clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Like a military valet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 That's right, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 But otherwise there was just you? There wasn't a cook or anybody else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, she used to superintend the cooking, but I had some hard work there. Hard work, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, I suppose she thought I could do it, you see, but it was really hard work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 You mean you think really she needed another person, or a bit more help?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, we really needed another one, really, yes. She used to help herself a good deal, she used to clear the breakfast table and while the
y were - I had our breakfast - and then when I went upstairs to do the beds and that sort of thing, well I didn't make her bed, she used to do her own bedroom. When I came down, oh, there was all this pile of dirty things to wash up in the kitchen, the sc
ullery, you know, and I felt I'd got a lot to do to do that. And then there was a room to be turned out every day between breakfast and lunch, or dinner - 'cos they didn't have late dinners, they had a midday meal and cold supper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And did she also have callers in the afternoon? Were your afternoons similarly to those at the schoolmaster's house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Oh, yes, I always had to be dressed by quite 3 o'clock. I always had to answer the door if visitors called and there was always a - this is all funny, but
 I can remember a good deal - there was a stand in the hall and there was a caller come and the ladies would see them and say 'in', you know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 That the people are in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Are in, the people are in, and if she be there she'd say 'out' and 
they'd say 'Is Mrs. Murphy in?' 'No, I'm sorry, she's out' and perhaps she was at home but she didn't want to see people, and I used to think that was strange. I used to go home and tell Mother and Father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And what did they think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 I used to tell them. It was very wrong, because that was when they didn't want to see them, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did you think that was dishonest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, I did in a way, but of course, the people who called would know just how it was because they treated the same, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 It was just the custom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
It was just the same. But when they were out there was always a card left and I was supposed to take a little silver tray, just a little round silver tray with the card on there, left in the hall and then when the peopl
e come home of when they come down if she was up in her room or anywhere she'd see who called, then they'd return that call, you see, as time when on. So I suppose if I could have married well off enough I should have known how to run a home (laughter). O
h, dear, I think about it now \{ILLEGIBLE\} today, do they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, a few people do, but it's not the usual thing, is it? What about the governess, did you get along with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Very well indeed, she was very nice. I couldn't understand all she said, of 
course, she taught English and she taught French, too. I forget her French name, what it was, but she was very nice.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What did you do in the evenings there? If you didn't go out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, I used to have one evening a week, but there was the supper for all of them to get and they had the tables laid very nicely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What time would that be that they had their supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 I think they used to have supper as far as I can remember about 8 o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And would you take quite a bit of time getting the supper ready and setting table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Well, I got things ready, you see, and of course they were in the drawing room, you see, so you'd got a sort of free hand to go and - if you felt you could do it best if you were all on your own, you see, than if th
ey were sitting in the room. And in the evenings the girls sometimes would be in their school rooms and sometimes they'd go up into Miss -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6258416\charrsid6102048  Walton}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  (?) I think was her name - the governess' room. But there was nothing much done after tea in the school room, no lessons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And after the supper what did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, I'd got the washing up to do and then we could go to bed when we liked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Would you do the washing up on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, mostly, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And so what time would you usually be finished in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, round about - between {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 9}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}}half past }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5513819\charrsid6102048 9{\*\xmlclose} and 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And you'd have been up in the morning what time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 About half past }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5513819\charrsid6102048 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 So it was a pretty long day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, a long day, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And was there any time in that day 
which was entirely your own time, you know when the lady of the house wouldn't have disturbed you, or asked you to do anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, I think in the afternoon, from the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}midday{\*\xmlclose} meal 'till teatime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Which was how long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, I say after the m
idday meal, but it was always about - we couldn't get round and tidied up until about - well, had to be before 3 because after 3 o'clock we didn't know who was going to call and at the best of times the ladies did call.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And teatime was what time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, teatime, they had what we call afternoon tea, not a spread out, just a cup in on a tray in the drawing room i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5513819\charrsid6102048 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  was, just in the drawing room. A tea tray and thin bread and butter, and then they used to have - a suppose there are them things about,
 you stand with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5513819\charrsid6102048 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
 tiers to them and you put your bread and butter on one and your cakes or something on the other and you carry them in, you know. That wasn't spread out on the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And would it have been about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5513819\charrsid6102048 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 16}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  o'clock{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5513819\charrsid6102048 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 16}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}
{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  o'clock{\*\xmlclose}, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 I'm trying to work out how much time in that long, long day, half past }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5513819\charrsid6102048 6}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  to say, 9.30, you had to yourself. Perhaps an hour, an hour and a half?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, yes, roughly. We used to get out of bed about 6 or half past. Well you could say that we didn't hav
e any free time, really, until - well, after the midday meal, perhaps, you'd had such a thing as a couple of hours, an hour and a half or a couple of hours until it was time to get things ready for supper, you see. They never had any hot suppers, it was j
ust - well, perhaps cold ham, tomatoes, cheese, biscuits and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And can you tell me about any other places you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, I told you that was the Rev. Murphy, they were military people, well then I went with some people by the name
 of Lynnallen, they were military people. Wherever did they go to? I can't think of the name of the place where they went to. Abroad somewhere. They were very nice people. She was a very, very young lady, his wife, and she was a very young lady. I did car
e a lot for her, really he was nice, Lynnallen, Captain Lynnallen. That was very nice house; Fridaywood Lodge was the name of the house, I don't know I you know it, it would be Berechurch way. They just kept }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8405883\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  of us; meself first parlour maid and a gardener
, and of course he had a groom to drive him round. There wasn't cars then, they had a horse and a high trap. He used to come and take them out, you know. I can't think where they went to, Bob Anyway, they went abroad somewhere. They were very nice people,
 very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 About how long were you with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, about a year and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And was your work there similar to what it had been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, similar, but I had more to do in the cooking line there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 How did you like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, I di
d like it, but I - when I went I think I told them (I'm not sure whether I've got mixed up with and another one) I told them I could work - in my reference they got from, for me, they said I was very methodical, and I}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5513819\charrsid6102048 \rquote m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  not now (laughter), very methodical 
and cooked nicely, but I wasn't extra special on fancy cakes, because they used to - in those times of day when they had afternoon tea in the drawing room sometimes, like, when you'd call they'd have fancy cakes and things. They usually bought those, but 
as time went on I made them, or I made some which they were pleased with and that was
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Can you remember anything else about that place? Were there any children there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Their first baby was born there when I was there, yes, their first baby and the
y christened it Joan. And I know what she said to the groom - you wouldn't like me to tell you that, would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What did she say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, this baby, she said - oh, she didn't say it to the groom. No, actually the groom heard her say that when he w
as driving her out. She said "we're calling her Joan", she said with a sneer, "I wish the little devil has been a boy", she said. "I wish the little devil had been a boy", she said, "we'd have called him Jack," she said, "but I've got near as I can to Jac
k, we're calling her Joan."
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Goodness! Poor little baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Lovely baby. Can't think where they went to. I can't think where they went They went right away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did you have anything to do for the baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, no! No, no. When the baby was born a
t the house, Fridaywood Lodge when they lived, and they had a trained nurse in for a month and when she went at the end of the month after the Missus left on her own, like, to get along, they had an experienced nurse to take the baby from the month, you s
ee, like they do - they used to then. An experienced to take her from the month, she had the entire charge of her then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Living in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes. She used to wear a grey uniform and she had to bath the baby and put to bed the regular time and kee
p the nursery clean. Yes, all that to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And how much did you have to do with her? Did you mix with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Oh, the lady, Mrs. Lynnallen, the lady, Mistress' name, she didn't like us to go in to see the baby. I used to sneak in when we went upstairs to do the beds, I used to like to look at the baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 But the nurse, did she eat with you, for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Well, she was very nice, but she was a bit reserved, but she had to be because the lady, Mrs. Lynnallen, didn't like us to go in to see the 
baby so much, you see. She didn't mix with us girls like the house parlour maid did, there were just I and the house parlour maid, you see. She didn't like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did she have her meals with the lady, Mrs. Lynnallen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, she had hers in the nursery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 So was she rather on her own then, the nurse?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, she was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And you? Whom did you have for company then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, the house parlour maid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And did you get on with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Got on very well with her, yes. We used to argue so
metimes. Oh, taking in on the whole, we did, but - well, young people today, you know, they would take that in, would they. They wouldn't think it was as so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 That sort of work, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did you get used to it? You said with your first job you were sad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Yes, well, we knew there was nothing else for us to do. Nothing else for you to do in those days. It was just to go to domestic service or - our mothers couldn't afford to keep us at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 After you got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5513819\charrsid6102048 12}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  pounds, did you ever go higher than that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, yes. Oh, yes. Yes, I think I got to 18 and 20.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Would that have been towards the end? It would keep going up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, I suppose it would, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 I think your husband mentioned that you were at Little Bromley Hall, too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 That was your last place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, my last place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What was that like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, they were very, very nice people, old-fashioned people. You know Little Bromley Hall? It burnt down, didn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 I just wondered because it was so very near, wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, that's right. A }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11933455\charrsid6102048 marvellous}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 That was near your own home, wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, yes, yes, quite near my own home. I left there when father and Mother I didn't go out any more. I stayed at home. W
e didn't marry 'till after Father and Mother had passed over, you see. They were very nice people, very old-fashioned, but everything had got to be just so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 When you say 'people were old-fashioned', what did it mean in those days?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 You thought they were old-fashioned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Well, yes. Well, for instance, they would - there they were old-fashioned people. If she was going to give a dinner party, it was a dinner party, a full course dinner and there'd be the soup, fish, and if not a joint - fowls th
en after that, a sweet. Sometimes the sweet was crossed out and they'd have a savoury, then biscuits and cheese, right away like that; and it had be done. Now when - those other places where I was with those other few people, they didn't have that. They h
ad more plain. And this Little Bromley Hall, it's a marvel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5513819\charrsid6102048 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
ous house, a most beautiful drawing room and of course, when I say 'old-fashioned', they'd got some of the old-fashioned furniture. You don't - well, I don't go anywhere to see it. You do occasionally hear about it, or see in the town. Some marve}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5513819\charrsid6102048 ll}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
ous furniture. They'd a huge drawing room and a dining room and a breakfast room. But when the old people were on their own they always mealed in the breakfast room, lived in there - had breakfast, dinner a
nd tea all in there. And by the way, you may not have heard of them. There's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8405883\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  Miss Nicholls at Broml}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5513819\charrsid6102048 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 y. They were daughters. No, no, no, I've got that wrong, haven't I
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 I know Nicholls at Lawford, Lawford Hall. Do you know them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, I've got mix
ed up with these Murrants, haven't I? No, these Miss Coopers that I'm talking - old Edgar Cooper - this place that I'm telling you, Little Bromley Hall. They were a big family, there was 10 of them,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7692508\charrsid6102048 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  children. One of them went to - I don't know if it was {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Australia
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. They were a very nice family. When I say that, of course, you don't understand what I mean - there wasn't any of this bumptious pride that there is with sort of some of the people today. Some of the people, if they've got 2 1/2d, more than I hav
e, they wouldn't speak to me. I wouldn't call that being sociable and grace, I call that being distant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And they weren't like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, they weren't a bit like that, no! But they were very, very strict. They had breakfast at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}8 o'clock{\*\xmlclose} and it had to be on the tick. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7692508\charrsid6102048 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}8}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  o'clock{\*\xmlclose} breakfast; }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7692508\charrsid6102048 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 13}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}1}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  o'clock{\*\xmlclose} dinner; and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7692508\charrsid6102048 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 17}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}5}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  o'clock{\*\xmlclose} tea; supper at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7692508\charrsid6102048 8}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  - nothing after supper, just the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}midday{\*\xmlclose}
 meal was hot. Joint, or whatever it the main meal and - joint and vegetables and a sweet and a savoury, perhaps. But if they gave a dinner party, it'd be dinner at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What other servants did they have in their house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, there was only the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7692508\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  of us and a woman in, poor old lady Barton. There was us }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7692508\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
 girls, we had to work hard and always had - well, there was a man 
to do all things outside to the windows, and a boy to bring in the coals and all like that. Big kitchen. It was a nice kitchen and a big outer kitchen. And there was - Oh, I don't know, let me see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5513819\charrsid6102048 There was 6 or 7 bedrooms, bathroom, corridors, of course and beautifully furnished.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And the Nicholls you mentioned, are they related to the Nicholls round }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5513819\charrsid6102048 
Lawford}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. J: No. That's another family.</subject}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7692508\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 >
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Once I was canvassing for the Labour Party round there and I met so
mebody that's how I heard tell of them. He said he'd worked for people called Nicholls at Lawford for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7692508\charrsid6102048 40}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
 years, or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. J: At Lawford Hall
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 That's right. That was the place he said, yes. I was canvassing round there once.</subject}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7692508\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 >
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mrs. J: Are they there now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. J: I believe so, yes. I believe some of them are there. They're very nice people. I worked for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 In your thatching, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 In thatching and other things as well. Yes, oh, yes, I worked for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 But you worked for some Miss Nicholls, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mrs. J: Well, for a time, at Murrants. Do you know where that is?</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, there's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8405883\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  Miss Nicholls, the daughter of Sir Ralph }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5513819\charrsid6102048 Nicholls}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  over here live at Broml
ey somewhere, Gt. Bromley, isn't there? (aside to Mr.)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr, J.: Yes, yes..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And what was your place like there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mrs. J.: Oh, anything. There was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8405883\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  of us - anything. I didn't like wasn't there long. It was more rough. But of course, it}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7692508\charrsid6102048 \rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  all down - well not down now, but they call it now ...</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. J: Murrant's Hall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mrs. J: Murrant Hall they call it now.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Whereabouts is that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mrs. J: Just across here somewhere. As you go from the Cross, you know Great Bromley Cross, on there to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
place}}Colchester{\*\xmlclose} ...</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. J: By the right and it's on the left. The name's on the gate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What was your favourite of all your jobs, do you think? Where were you happiest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mrs. J: Well, I don't quite know, I was happy so far at all of them. I don't quite know.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 You never had one where you were really unhappy, where you felt you were bad treated?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, no, not actually. Of course, I was very happy over at Bromley Hall because every time I com
e out, you see, I'd got me bicycle, I could go home. And when I lived out at Fridaywood Lodge I couldn't. I hadn't got a bicycle then, you see. And just the same with these military people that I lived, hadn't got a bicycle then. Still, I was happy there.
 Well, I knew I - well, there was times when I felt 'Oh, dear me, I wish I was at home', but I knew that was impossible, you couldn't be at home and earning money, could you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 So you just knew you had to accept it because it was all there was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
But I always was amused with one girl, but we used to take our money every month, and when she took her month's money she used to say, 'There, I'm going to buy ...' and she say what she was going to buy with it. She said 'I'm going to
 get a dress', those dresses they call them princesses. You wouldn't remember nothing about that, they were all buttoned up behind. She wanted that and she had one. She said, 'now, when I take my next month's money', said, 'I'm going to have ...', I forge
t what she'd say she'd have, she'd always plan what she'd buy every month. She never thought of saving a penny}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7692508\charrsid6102048 .}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
 It all went on clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What about you? What did you spend your money on? How did it go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Didn't go far. Well, frankly speaking, I didn
't let it go all on clothes. I was never so - well, plainly speaking, I wasn't so crazy on clothes. So long as I'd got something nice. I used to think, 'well, I'll have a new dress', or, 'I'll have a new coat, see if I can get that', but I used to save 1 
when I could, but there wasn't many to save. I don't know what I did with that first sovereign.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did you give any to your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, I used to make them little presents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 But you weren't living at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, no, I didn't live 
at home with Father and Mother. I'd got a good father and mother, oh, I had. They had to work very hard, Mother did. There was yes, there was a time when I went - was out at domestic service there was a sister and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8405883\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  brothers. The other - there was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7692508\charrsid6102048  1 or 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  other children which died before I could remember, but I had a sister, she died only about}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7692508\charrsid6102048 3 or 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  years ago, only her. And until this day I miss her, she lived at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5513819\charrsid6102048 Stowmarket}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  down in Suffolk.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Was she the one who was in service in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Colchester{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, t
hat's it, I only had her, yes. And my brother, my youngest brother, he died at 50-something, and my sister-in-law, his wife, lives next door. There now. Oh, we were a happy family. We }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5513819\charrsid6102048 
quarrelled}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What did your father do?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, well, he worked on the land. He worked on the land, really. Well, of course, you don't know the places, but there's a place called \{
BLANK\} Hall, just before you get to Ardleigh Station. Father worked there when we were children some of the time. Well, as time went on - You know where Mr. Erith live?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, I have passed his house. It's on the road as you go into Ardleigh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, we lived there, but it's been modernised since then. It's a farm, it was always a farm, belonged to the Abbotts. Well, Father went 
there as - well, they used to say in those days, you go rent free. That meant you'd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6102048  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7692508\charrsid6102048 go}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  to look after the stock on Sundays, the cows and the food feed the animals and all like that rent free. Well, you were jolly well paying for that, aren't you, by working
 all the Sunday, twice on Sundays. So we lived there, but of course since then that was sold and then, of course it was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7692508\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
 people who had it since Erith, did they? (aside to Mr. J.)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. J: No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mrs. J: Very fine. Miss Erith had it made nice. Do you know the Eriths</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, I don't know them really at all well. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5513819\charrsid6102048 What I know is that Mr. Erith'}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7692508\charrsid6102048 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5513819\charrsid6102048  got a brother who's an architect and I know his daughter, Lucy her name is, very, very well. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 I often go to her house. She's got a little girl about the same age as my little girl. I've met her mother and some of the older members of the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Mrs. J: Well, they're very nice people. Very nice people. Well, we think they are. Friendly. My husband goes up to the little shop occasionally there'
s a little shop up the road here, and he meets - very often has met Mrs. Erith in there and she stops and has a chat, same as anyone.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Not bumptious and proud.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, no, no. He met Mrs. Erith only }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7692508\charrsid6102048 2 or 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 , and - well, they're very nice people. Very nice people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 When you were living there - you know, what was Mr. Erith's place - was that when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 I was in domestic service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Would you go home on your off days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, I used to go there, yes, I used to go home
. Mother used to look after the fowls and make the butter. They kept cows, you know. Well, the latter part of the time. When we first went I don't think they kept cows.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 She made the butter for how many people? I mean how much butter would she make?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 She used to come and take it and then they sold it, you see. It belonged to Abbotts then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Could she keep butter for her own family back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, well, yes. They knew just how much butter you made, you see. Of course, you had to buy it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 She had to buy what she made.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And that was sort of part of the contract, was it, that your mother had to do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, yes, she had to look after the fowls, yes, and just the same with feeding the stock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And also look after her own family which was at that time living at home, which was who? Your sister was away, was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, there was us }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11156509\charrsid6102048 2 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 hildren, yes, and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11156509\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  brothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11156509\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  brothers at home with your mother to look after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, but my youngest brother, of course, he we
nt to school some of the time we were there. And my eldest brother, he didn't. He used to work on the farm or do anything - gamekeeper, do anything like that. Anything he could get hold of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did you have a happy childhood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, yes, yes. I wasn't
 always a good girl. When I was a little girl, I was a naughty girl once, ever so naughty, I was. Well, we went to school and there was a girl, I can tell you in a very few words, a girl my age. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5513819\charrsid6102048 We were always pally and coming home to school together, we w
ere not quarrelling, we were just having a bit of an argument and we used to take our dinners to school, there was no dinners at the school not to buy them, even, we had to take them - bread and butter and a piece of cheese, and sometimes she'd put some w
hat we call shortcakes or buns in for us, you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
We were coming hot from school and we were playing about and arguing and we - well, our dinner bag, well, Mother used to make them for us, when we wanted a new one she use to make us one, with handles. Well
 this girl - I don't know whether she was walking backwards or not, but anyway, I was swinging mine like that and caught her in the mouth. And I'd got a bottle in there - Mother used to give us some drink to take, tea or whatever it was, lemonade sometime
s - a it hit her in the mouth and knocked - I don't know whether it knocked }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11156509\charrsid6102048 1 or 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
 of her teeth nearly out. Oh, and it did bleed. I can see it coming um on that {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Ardleigh Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} now. Oh, I was sorry. We }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5513819\charrsid6102048 were not}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  quarrelling, you see, just an ordinary fun. Well
, I hadn't been home from school long before the people's name was Pitchall, they lived up on this little corner here not far from Eriths, just before you get to Eriths; and it was Jean, the girl too I hit with the bottle, she was with her mother and she 
w
as in tears, poor girl and her mouth was bleeding. She'd come to tell my mother what I'd done, you see. Oh, I was sorry. I was sorry, I can't tell you. She looked at me she said, 'You naughty girl, you'. Well, and I don't know what Mrs. Pitchall she was a
 
great - well, a neighbour of Mother's, you might say, and very friendly and all like that. But Mrs. Pitchall was a sensible woman, she knew my mother couldn't help what I'd done. However, that after tea she said, 'You get ready,', she said' and you go rig
h
t up to bed.' That was to me my Mother told me to go to bed. We had our tea, I went to bed and Mother always used to come up and say goodnight, and I can well remember it and I can see myself now. We were always taught to say our prayers, always, and I wa
s
 laying there and saying my prayers. I can see the bed now in my mind. And when I got up my mother said, 'yes,' she said,' you might well say your prayers.' And I never forgot it. That's one of the naughty things I did. Others have done things that's as b
ad, perhaps. And that poor girl, we were always friendly, she died at 18 and I saw her the morning she passed away. Always been friendly with her. But we were not quarrelling, you see. Stupid thing to do, isn't it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Was that the usual punishment your mother would give you, to send you up to bed when you were naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
I don't remember at all. But do you know - I don't aught to talk about this, but anyway. I listened to an article on the wireless, I think there's a lot of it going on now. A nurse an
d a doctor were talking about you should never punish a child by sending it to bed, they should always go to bed as a happy place, not for punishment, and I agree. I wasn't happy that night, I can tell you!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, you were punished enough by seeing how you'd hurt her, that was punishment enough, wasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
To go back to your work again. You said in your first place you didn't get anything but the tip, an occasional tip. In other places did you get anything extra?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, yes, when you went into gentlemen's houses - the most I think I had given me was 5/-, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11156509\charrsid6102048 5}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  for me and one for the house parlour maid. We each had then we thought it was a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What about anything else, food or clothes, were you ever given anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Oh, I don't know - I think I did once. What did I have given me once for clothes? I believe a young - I don't know what I did have given me once. Oh, I think I had a very nice black frock given me, it came from a lady but was no good to me,
 but I give it to Mother. I don't remember having anything great.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 But on the whole there weren't extras, except for an occasional tip, is that right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, that's right.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 I mean, it wasn't like your husband's father getting the wheat and that sort of thing, you just got your money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, no, that's it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 When you saved - you said you sometimes liked to save }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1710819 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 1 - where did you put it? Did you put it in the Post Office?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes. I remember the first }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1710819 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 1, I was going to put it in the Post Office; I walked right the way from}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11156509\charrsid6102048  Berechurch Lodge}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
 to Layer and they didn't keep a bank there. They didn't take any money, it was just a little sub-place. I went all that way to put }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1710819 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
1 away and then they wouldn't take it. I brought it back, I'd \{BLANK\} job for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 So what did you do with it then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 I saved it, but I quite forget where I put it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 You put it somewhere in your own room, or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 But as a general rule did you save in the Post Office?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Yes, I did, yes, yes. Or I used the Co-Op, used to buy some things at the Co-Op and you get yourself a divi, don't you, in the Co-Op. Some people say you have to pay more for your things, but I look at it in this light, you wouldn't save those shill
ings, perhaps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Can you tell me when you had your first home, I think your husband said last week it was the home that your parents had had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 That's right, yes, that's right. They both passed over and the landlady were known, of course, ever since
 we were children, used to go to her farm for milk and then my husband saw her and after Father and Mother passed over he took over, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And can you tell me something about it? You did say last week, I think, there it had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8405883\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  bedrooms, is that right? And a front room and a kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, can you tell me how your life was changed in a way when you started your own home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, of course, I missed Mother because living in the same house - but there was no chance
 in those days of getting a cottage anywhere else. No chance, mean, if there was a cottage to let anywhere and a man wanted it - a farmer wanted it to put a man in to work for him, well my husband, you see, that is now, I mean, he didn't work for anybody 
to go and want to live under him, you know what I mean. So we lived there and we shared some of the things - of course, Mother's things were old, you know, very old, old-fashioned some of them, but still.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did you say you shared out some of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Well, we did in some ways. That old clock was my mother's. Yes, I'd been going to - American - I'd been going to have that - well, my husband did do it once so that it should strike. It should go, shouldn't it. Well, I tell you what my mother had got and 
I've often wondered - because we didn't quarrel over them, my sister wasn't well - well, we didn't think much of it then, a chest of drawers with brass handles. A chest of drawers, you know what I mean, don't you? And the handles were - you didn't just pu
ll it out, the handles was like a ring and I can remember us children liked to pull it up like that and let it bang down to jingle. There was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11156509\charrsid6102048 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  long drawer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11156509\charrsid6102048 , 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
 long drawers the width of the chest of drawers and one each side, and never knew what happened to it. Well, my sister had it, but when}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11156509\charrsid6102048  she passed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  over some of the things were sold. She had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11156509\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
 boys. Some of the things they shared and what happened to the others I don't know. I don't know really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 When you say you missed your mother, did you feel her presence in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, yes and no, if you understand that. I felt - everything was different, of course, everything was different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And you'd been living there all the time, hadn't you, for a while? Looking after her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, we lived there - how long did we live there, Bob?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. J: A good }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11156509\charrsid6102048 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, I mean before you gave up service. You said, I think, after Little Bromley Hall you went to look after your old people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, they were ill at the time, off and on, and I never went out any more, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 How many years was that, then, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. J: It was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11156509\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  years, I reckon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 About }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11156509\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
 years. And then after you took it over as your own place and lived there, was that straight after the wedding, you moved in straight away? Or did you have another place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mrs. J: No, we went there, didn't we?</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. J: Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Can you tell me about your daily routine, say, in the first year you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mrs. J: Oh, dear. Oh, I believe I was
 only talking about it the other day somebody who come round. Monday was washing day, and Tuesday I used to leave for mangling and ironing and getting the linen away; Wednesday, bedrooms; Thursday, my front room; Friday and Saturday, kitchen and cooker. B
ut then all wiped out today - anyhow today, I can't do it today. I can't work like that today.</subject2>
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did you bake your own bread, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, no. Oh, no, I couldn't do that!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 I mean in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mother did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 When you first started your married life, did you bake?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Oh, no, no. Only bake my own cakes and things. I was very fond of cooking. But my mother baked bread, but of course, not in the last year she was alive she wasn't well enough, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And did you make anything else in the house? Clothing, or bottling or preserving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, only cakes and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Not jam or marmalade?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, yes, jam. Oh, yes. That was a harvest. I've }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5513819\charrsid6102048 seen one}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  of the cupboards up in the room there piled up with jam, all sorts. Now today, I haven't made any jam this last year or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8405883\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 . Everybody seem to buy it, don't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What about sewing, did you do any sewing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, no, I do just a bit of me own, not to take in sewing. I couldn't make dress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, I mean I also wondered if you'd made curtains.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, those sort of things, you could do that. You could do your own, just bit by the yard and make them, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And in the morning, then, you did your housework, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 You get up about what time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, I used - my husband used to go out for the day, so I used to pack up his food, you see. I used to get up about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11156509\charrsid6102048 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 , was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. J: Yes, before then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mrs. J: Before }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11156509\charrsid6102048 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 , sometimes.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 How did you get up, did you have an alarum clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No! Oh, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Just woke?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. J: Yes, just woke.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And you'd pack up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Used to pack up his food. Well, of course, there was only the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11156509\charrsid6102048 4}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  rooms nice sized rooms and the kitchen - we lived in our kitchen, nice little kitchen, there was just room. We could - room for us to have our meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Would you have breakfast together in the mornings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, no, no, my husband used to have his cup of tea. And I believe when we were first married, didn't you have cocoa made with milk?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. J: Quite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
When we first married, but after that he always used to have a cup of tea and bread and butter before he went. Oh, I used to have my bit of breakfast on me own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 After he'd gone off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Both: Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Any time then. And I used to get about me work and I'd got me bicycle if I wanted to go out for a ride I'd go after I'd done me work.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did you often do that? Did you like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, I - not every day, but I used to go out a good bit on my bicycle, had some old friends -
 they've passed over now - I used to go and see there perhaps once a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did you ever go riding with a friend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well no, I don't know - well, yes, I have occasionally, but not often. We used to go out on our bicycles, didn't we? (to husband)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. J: Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 When would you go out together on your bicycles, at a weekend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 At weekends. Saturdays we occasionally went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Colchester{\*\xmlclose}
. Sundays we used to go out occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And your husband wouldn't come home for lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And so you'd have your lunch on your own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, that's right, and then have a meal at night. Of course, we told you about the puddings his mother used to make.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did you keep on the same kind of foods?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, well, no, not quite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 How did you differ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Well, we used to have a small piece of - well, a nice little piece of beef Of course, it's a - for roast for the weekend. We generally used to have a piece of sirloin, well today you can't get a sirloin, it'd be a tremendous price.
 A small piece of sirloin, perhaps a Yorkshire pudding - you know what they are, I suppose - a Yorkshire pudding and vegetables. We used to have that more often than not hot on Saturday. Sunday morning we used to go to church or chapel. And I used to do s
ome bacon on Friday, we used to have apply tart and custard, perhaps, to make ready for Sunday. And then sometimes we went out to tea with some friends and sometimes we had friends }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11156509\charrsid6102048 to }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 tea. That was on Sunday, and that was that. And during the week, well,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11156509\charrsid6102048  the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  piece of beef we had used to last 'til we were sort of - well, when it was finished up we could go to the butchers and get something else that we wanted}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11156509\charrsid6102048 .}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  Of course, there wasn't so much money about, but things were not the price they are today. Terrible, isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 But that way of having the meat and then having it the next few days, had their been the way your mother had done it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And what would you do in the afternoons, in the weekdays when your husband was out at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Well, I don't know. Sometimes I'd have a read, or - and there were some neighbours round about, we used to get in the garden and have a chat, that sort of thing. They were happy days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 You didn't have to do housework in the afternoons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, there was no need. I mean, I could do it all in the morning, like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did you enjoy being with the neighbours and that sort of thing? Were you friendly with people around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, yes, yes. Old friends that we'd got there when we passed over, haven't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. J: Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Were there any social events you went to? There were the anniversaries, which were the great thing, weren't they? Were there any other things, any women's organisations you belonged to and things like that at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
No, there wasn't, I don't think so, not in my time. But when I was a child I remember my mother going to what they called the 'Mother's Meeting', and that was down at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}
Ardleigh{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Church{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. Some people used to run it from there at the Parish, what they call th
e Parish Room, and you could take your sewing. And I remember my mother used to go, and before I went to school, this was, used to go with Mother and they used to - there was a lady there (she was Miss }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5513819\charrsid6102048 Nicholls}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 ), she used to read to these women. Anybody co
uld go and you could take your children, and that. I used to go with Mother, that's before I went to school. And this Miss }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5513819\charrsid6102048 Nicholls}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 , she used to give the children (if there were children there) picture books to look at, or a doll to nurse and were thrilled
 with it, of course. But there was no institutes, or anything like that like there is today, oh, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 You didn't go to the Mother's Meetings yourself, when you grew up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, No, well, they were finished then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Could you tell me about your actual wedding? Did you have it in Church or Chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Church. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5513819\charrsid6102048 Reverend Grabb, of course, he was a very, very sociable man. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Very sociable indeed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Do you mind telling me why you were married in the Church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, I don't know. This place has a li
cence for marriages, but I don't know why, but my mother always used to - years ago this place wasn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5513819\charrsid6102048 licenced}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
 for weddings, for marriages, but it is now, and it was at the time we married. And the minister, the head minister that conducted this place, he 
said after it was licenced for marriages he would give to the first couple that married a nice Bible. Well, there was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4488453\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
 got married, wasn't there? (to husband)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. J: Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And my husband's brother was one, so they got a Bible - who was the other one? (to husband)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. J: Charlie Jaggard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Mrs. J: Charlie Jaggard. Another Jaggard. So they each had a nice Bible But my mother .... I don't know .... wasn't too much about it ... Mother always felt that the Church was the proper place to be m
arried. I don't think it makes so much difference, but Mother was brought up to the Church that the went. She used to go to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Ardleigh{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Church{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} as a girl. She used to tell me that and I quite believed her. But she did, she used to go to the Church there, and t
hat's why we were married at Ardleigh Church, and from there we went down to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5513819\charrsid6102048 Stowmarket}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
, my sister was married then, and we had a party my sister's.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What was that like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Very nice. Quite a lot of them and I suppose - several of them have pass}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4488453\charrsid6102048 ed
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  over, now, haven't they? (to husband)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. J: They have, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mrs. J: Just a family party.</subject2>
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 About how many people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 We had a cold ... well, I suppose we'd call a dinner cold - fowls, I got them all ready and they w
ere - yes, I think there was somebody come and go them, I don't know what, before the wedding. We had fowls and ham and all the rest of it. Everything nice, nice as they do it today but perhaps not I don't know, I don't see why it shouldn't be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And did you have anything to drink for the wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, yes, there was wines and for lunch there was ale, I think, for dinner, rather. And then there was wines in the evening, if you \{
ILLEGIBLE\} or a glass}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4488453\charrsid6102048  of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  spirit for those that liked it or there that didn't, we had a very nice time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Friends and family, or just family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. J: And friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mrs. J: Yes, yes.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And did you have any dancing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, No, there wouldn't have been room, would there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. J: There wouldn't have been room. It was just a cottage, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mrs. J: My sister had got a nice little house, though, better than what you get in the country. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4488453\charrsid6102048 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  rooms, just }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4488453\charrsid6102048 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
 bedrooms and usual downstairs, you know.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And then you went to your own home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 We stayed a couple of days, didn't we?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. J: No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mrs. J: We didn't come home that day Bobby.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. J: We come home the Sunday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mrs. J: No, we come home the Monday morning. I'll tell you why, we met Mr. Harris 
going on post duty. He said, "Well, got back, then?" Remember It?</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. J: Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mrs. J: Not very exciting.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And what did you wear on your wedding day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Grey. A grey. Of course, we married in the June and Mother died in the when did Mother die, Bob? Father died in the Christmas, didn't he?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. J: Yes, and your mother died in May.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 May. And we married in the June. Oh, I had ever ... oh, I thought it was grey alpaca frock - dress - had it made, and a grey hat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Any flowers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, yes, a nice bunch of flowers, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And so it was new clothes specially for the wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, oh, all new, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did you go by the old rhyme? You know the old rhyme, 'something old, something new'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No I don't think we ... no I don't think I did. No, I don't think so. I' not superstitious that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 You don't have any superstitions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No. Do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No. I don't have any, but my mother does. And you see, when I got married she sent me a blue garter,
 you know the old fashioned garters? And she said 'you must wear this on your wedding day or you'll have bad luck.' And I thought what nonsense. But I wore it just to please her. She was in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Africa{\*\xmlclose}
 you see, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4488453\charrsid6102048 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  thousand miles away, so she couldn't come to my wedding, which sad for her. But I'm not superstitious at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
My sister was, you know. I don't know how she was. Yes, she was superstitious. Different things she said, she said if you upset salt on the table there was sure to be some unpleasantness, 
and - oh, I forget what else different things. 'Oh,' I said, 'nonsense!"
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 At the actual ceremony there was yourself, of course, and your husband, and who else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 My sister's husband give me away and my sister-in-law was sort of the maid of honour. 
That's all. We had a very quiet - very quiet in the Church. was glad when it was all over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well - I don't like going to weddings now, even.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Were you actually born }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4488453\charrsid6102048 in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Africa{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes. I came here in 1958, and my parents live there, in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
country-region}}South Africa{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. No you said last week that when you were with the schoolmaster and his wife, Mr. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1710819 &}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
 Mrs. Brown, they used to take you out at the weekends, all of you together used to go out and have tea in a house in the country. What sort a house was that? What was it like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 It was a country post office.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Tell me more about it. What was it like?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, it's all I could say about that, really. It was the post office and a living accommodation, and they looked after the post office.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And they sold teas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
You ordered your tea. It wasn't really a restaurant, but they would do that for people taking a country walk in the afternoons, like the closing days in the town on Thursday, and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Would you order it in advance, or when you got there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Oh, I think he used to just write and tell them, he and his wife and how many children would be going for tea. Just tea, bread and butter and a few little cakes. Not an elaborate tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 But you couldn't just arrive there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 But could anybody write, or did you have to be known to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 That I couldn't say, whether they knew the people or not. I think they would do that for anyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 But they liked to have warning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Were there other places like that at that time, where people used to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, I couldn't say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did any of your other employers take you with them on an expedition?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, we used to go for a - to the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Camp{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Church{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, to see the soldiers come out on parade. At the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Camp{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Church{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, different regiments go out and another lot come in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And would you have any refreshment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, not there, it was just the walk to....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Were the Browns the only people who would take you out and then have refreshment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, yes, they were the only people. Yes, the only people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
All these people that you worked for, you know, when you were in domestic service, when you stopped working for them they often went away, like the Murphys went to Nova Scotia and that sort of thing. Did
 you ever work for people and live them for some other reason? I mean not because they went away? Did you leave some of your own free will, to go to another place?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes ... I can't think of the doctor's name.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 It doesn't matter if you don't remember the name.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 I can't remember ... I know it quite well ... a Doctor Lessano.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 In {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Colchester{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Yes. But when we were leaving a situation we had to give a month's notice and I did that there. A very hard place. The lady was very nice, but he wasn't. He wasn't very nice to his wife, either. And so I left for various reasons, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did they have children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 One little girl - Valentine her name was. She was born on Valentine's Day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And how old was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, she went to a private school. I should think when I was there she was about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13720733\charrsid6102048 8 or 9}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 , I should think. Very nice little girl.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Why was it a hard place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4488453\charrsid6102048 Well, they only kept me, and they had a man come in the mornings to do the rough work, like cleaning knives and 
boots and pump up the water and all that sort of thing. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Very hard it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And when you gave in your notice did they accept it without any fuss?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, yes. The lady told me, she said she was very sorry, asked me for my reasons and I thought, well I'd like a better situation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Can you remember what you were getting there in the way of money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1710819 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 15 a year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And can you remember when that was, about what date? If you could remember how old you were, roughly speaking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, I should think ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Was it quite a long time after you were at the Rev. Murphy's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 I should think I was about 18.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did you find that in your positions you gradually went up? Because I remember you said the Rev. Murphy's wife took you up from }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1710819 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 10 to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1710819 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 1
2. Then your next position after that, was it at Fridaywood Lodge, and was there somewhere else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Where did I go after the Murphys? I think they were military people. I'm not sure if was Captain Lynnallen. Yes, Captain Lynnallen.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, you told me a little about those. Were those the people at Fridaywood Lodge?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 So when you go on to a new place, would you ask for what you'd been getting before, or would they ask you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 They would ask me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 How would they say, for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, they'd say, you get that for a start and then see how you progress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 They would usually start you, would they, on what you'd had before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, yes, mostly, yes. But if you asked a wage and you felt they were anxious to engage you, they would give you what you ask, see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did you ever go down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Never, no, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did you ever, after you'd left people, keep in touch with them in any way, or did they keep in touch with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 They did, the Murphys. She wrote
 me a very nice letter and said how her husband had got thrown from his horse and killed. No, I don't think - no I don't think I got into touch with anyone else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 So after you'd say goodbye, that was goodbye for good, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 For good, yes. That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did you ever miss the children at these houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 I did miss the children, the little girls that I had at the Browns, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 But you didn't see them again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 You've no idea what happened to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, I had
 - well, yes, yes. Ina, the eldest one, she was a school governess, and - most extraordinary thing - I saw her .... she wrote a letter, I think it was in the Essex County Standard, it was some years ago, because I thought 'well, I know where Miss Ina is n
o
w, I'll write to her', but I never did that. But they lost their mother and their father, but what happened to ... she wrote a letter and I can't remember what that was on, but she was great on writing. They educated the girls well, you see. She was great
 on writing. And I was so pleased when I saw her name in the paper an always intended to write to her, but I didn't do so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 How long ago was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 How long is it now? Since we've lived here it must be.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13720733\charrsid6102048 30}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  years ago, or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13720733\charrsid6102048 20 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 years ago?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, yes, I should think it must be - since we've lived here I can go back }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13720733\charrsid6102048 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  years, quite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Had she not married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 She wasn't married then, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 So she had her maiden name, Brown? And she lived in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Colchester{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Brown, yes. She lived in Colchester.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And the other sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Vera? I didn't hear anything about her, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 When you worked with the Rev. Murphy, did they have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Every morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And you went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4488453\charrsid6102048 dining room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  - the bells ring - every morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And did anybody else that they employed go to the service there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Yes, Captain Lynnallen, they always had morning prayers. Always. The Capt. Lynnallen's mother, she was a very religious woman, very religious.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did she live with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, she used to come there for her holiday. They used to live at - is there a place called Westlynn, or Eastlynn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, Eastlynn. In {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Norfolk{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
? Somewhere round there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 That was their home. And Cap. Lynnallen and his wife, when they had their holid
ay, went to stay there. And then we had our month's holiday, the maid
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 A month, you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Were you paid for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And when you had family prayers, did everybody who was employed in the house go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, all t
he maids and myself and the nurse and the house parlour maid. And Cap. Lynnallen, he read the prayers and the lesson. And I can see the old lady now, his mother, sitting in a big armchair with her head bowed very severely. And us girls used to kneel down 
on the .. near the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4488453\charrsid6102048 dining room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  table or the chairs, wherever we - in the room. Never missed them, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did you have any choice? I mean suppose you had not been religious and hadn't wanted to go, what would have happened, do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, I don't know. There wasn't any dispute or anything said about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 So everyone just went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 When we first went they said, 'well, we have family prayers every morning immediately after breakfast' - in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4488453\charrsid6102048 dining room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 , before the table was cleared.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And anyone else do you remember having them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, I don't, only those. Capt. Lynnallen and the Rev. Matthew, that's all
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 When you were with the Rev. Murphy, did you also have your {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}
{\xmlattrvalue 12}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}midday{\*\xmlclose} meal with the family? \{BLANK\} as you had done at the Brown's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, no! No, they had - no, we had it in the servants' hall, or kitchen. The governess had it with the girls in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4488453\charrsid6102048 dining room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Were there any other places you had where you ate with the family, besides the Browns?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Why was that, do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Well, I thought - whether they thought maids were not well enough behaved, we were taught to behave if we were poor (laugh). I don't know why.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Why do you think the Browns were different from the others in that respect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, y
ou see they were not so well to do. They weren't moneyed people. was just an ordinary schoolmaster at an ordinary school. Well, when I say 'ordinary people', he just worked at that school and had an ordinary school wage. And his wife before they were marr
ied, they were tailors, big tailor in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Colchester{\*\xmlclose}
. Her name was Nicholson, Miss Nicholson and she was a wonderful singer. Not after she married she didn't go, but before she was married she used to sing at concerts and that sort of thing, although I never heard her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And so she herself, when she'd been a child, the family weren't wealthy either you don't think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, no. Just ordinary tailor's shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 You said usually people didn't have late dinner. Most of the people you worked for didn't have a late dinner, they had a 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}midday{\*\xmlclose} dinner. Is that so
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}
{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}Midday{\*\xmlclose} meal, yes. It was the military people that had the late dinners. Except Sunday nights when it was called supper. Yes, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}midday{\*\xmlclose} meal about, It's not quite sure if it was one or 1.30. Lunch they called that, lunch. But at night dinner was generally 7 o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And it was the cold supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, military people had the hot dinners {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 19}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}7 o'clock{\*\xmlclose}, except Sundays and then it was cold supper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Would that have been Capt. Lynnallen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 He had late dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And what about the Murphy's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, they had {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}midday{\*\xmlclose}, because of the children. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}
{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}Midday{\*\xmlclose} because of the children, and cold supper at 8 o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 But the people at Little Bromley Hall, they had the dinner in the middle of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Middle of the day, yes. Very, very old-fashioned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What about entertaining? I think you mentioned last week when you were at Little Bromley Hall they had these dinners at night with about }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13720733\charrsid6102048 5}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  courses, or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What about other people? Did any of the other people entertain that you worked for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, not - no. Sometimes they'd have what you call a Bridge Party, but nothing more, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What would happen at the bridge parties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well ... I couldn't tell yo
u what time they would start that. Well, then there was refreshments in the breakfast room. Just refreshments handed round in the breakfast room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 You would hand them round, would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, the house parlour maid did. I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 You prepared the things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, all cold, you know. All cold, sandwiches and such like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And what would they drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Oh, all sorts of things. I don't know. Soda water and whisky, some of the and lemonade and those sort of things. Coffee, sometimes coffee.
\par 
