 selves would make the half dozen. Then after that they would have a smoke and coffee in the drawing room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What about big parties? Did anyone ever have a large party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, no, I don't think so. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Do you ever remember anyone having dancing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No. These military people would go out to a dance. They got invited out to a dance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And children's parties, do you remember any parties for children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No. No, no children's parties. There were no children - these }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13720733\charrsid6102048 2}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  girl}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13720733\charrsid6102048 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
 at the Rev. Murphy's they were too old for children's parties. They used to go away for a holiday, you see, in the summer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What about the little girls Ina and Vera Brown? Did they have parties at a
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, just a little school party, they invited their little friends in, perhaps }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13720733\charrsid6102048 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  of them to make up a half a dozen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 At a birthday time would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Birthday times, yes. Yes, one was - one's birthday was in June and I think the other one ... I can't remember when the other one was.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Who called on Mrs. Murphy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Military people. I don't remember their names. It's all military people. Well, som
e. Perhaps they were not all military people, but what we would call - well, what we would call well to do people. People in their own class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And you mentioned that other schoolmaster's wives would call on Mrs. Brown?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, just occasionally. There was a schoolmaster and his wife, their names was {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Wilson{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, but when they first came to visit Mr. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1710819 &}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
 Mrs. Brown they were not married. They were married after that, and then they went away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Do you remember any other callers they had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did they have a smaller social circle, do you think? Then the military people
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, I think they did. Well, yes they did. There were some people by the name of Aldridge who used to call on Mr. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1710819 &}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  Mrs. Brown. They lived in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Barrack Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Colchester{\*\xmlclose}, and I believe he worked in a big, big candle factory. He was something to do - one of the head ones in this big, big factory. I can't tell you where.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What sort of work? Would he be an overseer, do you think? Or what would have done in the factory?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Well, I don't know - candle - I don't know what they would do. Yes, a candle factory - I don't know - he would be one of the authorities, he wouldn't be one of the ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 He wouldn't be working on the shop floor sort of thing, do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
No, he wouldn't do that, no. But as time when on, it's the most extraordinary thing, it was after I got married I think we heard, he was made Mayor of Colchester, this Mr. Aldridge, and his wife was Mayoress of Colchester. And they didn't keep a big - it 
was a big house, but they only kept a couple of maids.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 They didn't live in a grand manner?)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 It is very interesting, you see, seeing what social life was then. Do you think people kept to a smaller sphere of life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, that's it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What was the name of the people at Little Bromley Hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Cooper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And my husband said to ask you, was he the local squire. Is there anyone round there who was called the squire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Squire? No, no. There was Mr. Edger Cooper and the
n, of course, there was the vicar. The vicar was - what was his name? Can't think of his name. Oh, no, there was no squire. There was - well, there were some very well to do people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 But not one chief one?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No. Cope was the vicar's name. The Rev. Cope, at the Little Bromley vicarage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
When you went home to look after your parents the last few years of their lives, you'd said earlier that your mother couldn't afford to keep you - you know, you had to go into service, people didn't have enough m
oney in those days to keep their daughters at home - how did you manage for money then, when you went to look after your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 We shared ... we shared the family ... what there was, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 But was there a little bit more to share then, that you were able to stay at home to look after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, yes, you see, my - yes, I'd got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13720733\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  brothers at home and they brought in a little, you see, payment for their board as we used to call it, you see and my father until he was too ill to do it, kept 
pigs, and he reckoned on making a little money out of the pigs. Mother kept fowls until such a time as she couldn't look after them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 So you didn't feel very much worse off then, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, no, I was happier to be at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What did your brothers do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Oh, well, my eldest brother was a gamekeeper most of his time, and my younger brother when he first went to work he went on the farm, various farms. And then there was a time when he worked with my husband for a bit. Then after that he wor
ked with the builders in Colchester.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Are either of your brothers living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
No, no, they've both passed over. Yes, both passed over. My younger brother, he died when he was about 50 and his wife lives in the cottage just beyond here, now. And her children were born in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4488453\charrsid6102048 Stowmarket}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 , so she knows }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4488453\charrsid6102048 Stowmarket}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
You said you had some friends in the village that you used, sometimes, to go over and see after you were married, on your bicycle. Who were they? Had you known them many years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, we'd got some friends at Layer de la Haye, through {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Colchester{\*\xmlclose}
. We use to go and see them and go and stay a night. Once or twice we did. Where else did we go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Had they always lived there? Or had they formerly lived in Ardleigh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, no they always lived in Layer. I met them through going to the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Methodist{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Church{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} when I lived at Fridaywood Lodge. That's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6102048  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Fridaywood, Layer de la Haye. And the young lady that played the organ there, I correspond with her now. She's getting on for 80, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Is that more than 50 years ago, when you were at Fridaywood Lodge?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, some of it's over - oh, yes, we've been married over }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13720733\charrsid6102048 50}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  - some of it's over }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13720733\charrsid6102048 50}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  years ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And you'd go over sometimes, would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, I haven't been for a long time. But we've cycled over there since we been here. We've cycled over to Layer de la Haye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And was she married, your friend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, she was married - but I don't think I could tell you all of this, it rather sad. Her people had a house built - well she
's living in it now. She married comfortably off. Her husband made her a nice home. Her mother was very ill. She went home to look after her mother and the husband might have gone there to live because the house was big enough, but he just wouldn't go and
 she felt - oh, she told me a piti}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13720733\charrsid6102048 ful story about it. She just fe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13720733\charrsid6102048 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
 it was her duty to keep with her mother, to cling to her mother rather than husband. She asked me did I agree and I said 'no!' See what I mean, she married the man, she had}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13720733\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  children, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13720733\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  - of course, this doesn't come into it, I know, but she had }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13720733\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  children, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13720733\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  nice children, and one of them died, and I did think after that (because her husband and herself, of course went to the funeral), I thought they would have come together again, but the never did. It was a broken marriage.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 When you used to go over and stay with them, was it broken then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
No, I didn't stay with them, not there. No, they were an old family that I stayed with, their name was Hayhoe. They were very nice. They attended the church I went to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 They were also at Layer de la Haye, were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What about friends in Ardleigh, did you have many friends there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, we knew everybody in Ardleigh, but I don't say we were all friends, but we knew most all the Ardleigh people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 If you went out shopping you'd sort of greet everybody that you saw?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And they would do the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, yes, certainly, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 But when you mentioned that sometimes you'd go out in the afternoon and see}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6102048  }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4799013\charrsid6102048 the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  friend, would that be locally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Well, yes, it would. The other lady, she's passed away now. Yes, I used cycle, and it wasn't far away, to see her. And then another one not far away from us, I'd see her perhaps once a week. Each of them once a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4799013\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  old ladies you'd see?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes. And the daughter of one of these old ladies is in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Clacton{\*\xmlclose}
 now, I correspond with her. She's 86. So we've kept in touch with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4799013\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And when you used to go and see the one in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Clacton{\*\xmlclose}
's mother, was the daughter at home, too? I mean, would you see the mother and the daughter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, the daughter was - no, she was married and got a house in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Colchester{\*\xmlclose}
. And after - when she married a man in a milk business and they had their own house built and after that they sold it and retired and went to Clacton to live and they're there now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Do you ever go and see her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, I haven't seen her for a long time. She used to come here every summer and see us, but she's been crippled up wi
th rheumatism and arthritis, goes about in a wheelchair. But see, we've kept in touch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 How many correspondents do you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 How many letters did I say I'd got to write? And I managed to get }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4799013\charrsid6102048 2}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  done yesterday in the morning. Oh, Honestly, I don't like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 You don't like writing letters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
No. It's nice to have friends, and Christmas time when you get off cards a things, and that sort of thing, oh, yes. I like to get a letter and I like to write to them. We look at the weekly paper, if ther
e's anyone passed out that I knew for a long time I write them, although I don't like writing. I don't like writing, but I write - I can - I don't write all plainly speaking \{BLANK\}
 but I can put a letter together, but my writing is shocking. Shocking, my writing is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 It's quite legible, though, it's quite easy to read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
I've got a friend - it's rather an insult, really, she told me ... I've known her ... I went to school with her ... she's my husband's age, and when I wrote to her once, when she w
rote back, she said 'I'm sure you can write better than that if you tried!" She said, 'I'm so glad we've got a good postman,' she said, 'otherwise I wouldn't get your letters." (laugh) Well, didn't mean to - if I took offence, because I didn't take offenc
e
. I've written to her since. I'll tell you, she was ... used to be between maid a Ardleigh Park, I've known her a good while, and she told me there she got a shilling a week. Her father was coachman there and she said, 'but I never saw the shilling,' she 
said, 'it was put in Dad's pay packet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And she's still living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, yes, yes. She went out to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Oldham{\*\xmlclose}, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
Lancashire{\*\xmlclose}, after her father - her people died at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Ardleigh{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Park{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, she went out to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Lancashire{\*\xmlclose} and married out their. She lost her husband, now she's come to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Ipswich{\*\xmlclose}
 to live with a married daughter. Her married daughter, they're comfortably off, they've been to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}America{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. I said to her one day, I said, 'that's where the money is, isn't She said, 'Yes, but you've jolly well got to work for it.'
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Do you ever feel you'd like to go and visit any of these friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Well, these friends - it's their own fault we haven't been. They've asked us to go to see them. They've got a beautiful car and they would come and fetch us, out they keep - in summer the
y put if off and said 'We'll wait 'till another time'. I'm not keen on going out. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 You'd rather stay home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, yes, and I've got plenty to do and it's a big old place, I can't do me work properly and I've had leg trouble this winter, and - 
I've felt well, you want your legs good to get about, don't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Would you say that your friends and your husband's friends were the same people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 You shared your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, yes, we did. When we were younger you see, we were - we were both born in Ardleigh and grew up ... and we went to 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Ardleigh{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. We went to the same church on Sundays, you see, and that's it. Yes, we were all - I have had friends, perhaps, when I was in domestic service that my husband's got t
o know through me, you see. Those people at Layer I met - he met through them (she must mean 'me'), you see, me going to the church there I'm these friends, and that was that, and they became friends to all of us. Another thing I used to do when we were m
a
rried on a Sunday was, we used to have a - the minister used to come, perhaps, once every so often and then they had what they call a lay preacher and we used to take it in turns to entertain them to dinner on a Sunday when they came, you see. Of course, 
t
hey were all Church of England people. Well, this lady friend that I've been telling you that I used to visit, she said to me one day, she said, 'couldn't you manage,' she said, 'I'm going out for a holiday' she said, 'couldn't you manage to take my turn 
h
aving the preacher?' 'Oh,' I said, 'I couldn't entertain the minister - the preacher.' 'Oh, yes, ' she said, 'you can.' Well, I did and after that I took my turn and do you know, I just dreaded when the head minister was coming because I thought 'I can't 
entertain him. I can't entertain him, just humble people like ourselves.' But I managed it, and I carried on \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 finished off, and I suppose they all passed over now, and I used to enjoy having them. And as a matter of fact I enjoyed having the mini
ster rather than some of the lay preachers. because a lot of these lay preachers thought they were it. But the minister they were educated and they knew what was what, and they were people as could mix with anyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And that was Sunday dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname 
Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}midday{\*\xmlclose} dinner, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 How often did your turn come up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 About once in about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4799013\charrsid6102048 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  weeks, there were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4799013\charrsid6102048 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
 of us, you see. We never knew who we were going to have, actually, unless we had the plan read out to us telling us who we were going to have. And 
I always remember the first preacher I had, always. He was a schoolmaster, that's the funny thing about it. He was a schoolmaster, and do you know, at that time I'd got one of my sister's boys, the youngest boy, staying with me. It was in the summer holid
ays, and they used to get }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4799013\charrsid6102048 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
 weeks' holiday, and of course, they used like to come and spend their holidays with us, these boys. So I said to my nephew - oh, I don't know how old he'd be, perhaps about 12 - I said, 'Arthur', I said, 'I've got the minister co
ming - the preacher coming on Sunday dinner,' I said, 'You will behave yourself, won't you?' Which I needn't have said because my sister was most particular the way they were brought up. So he said, 'Yes, 'course I shall'. This is awfully funny, you know,
 to tell you this. I remember very well what I'd got - 'cos they didn't have hot dinner. I'd got a piece of roast loin of pork, apple sauce potatoes, and I forget what I'd got after - apple tart, custard and cream.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And it was all cold?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 For dinner - for lunch ... well, dinner time, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 But was it all cold?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
All cold, yes, except potatoes. Of course, we had hot potatoes always with we did in domestic service. Now, I'd said to this boy, 'you behave yourself so after this was all over 
- I don't know if this was on the Sunday evening or what - Arthur, my nephew said to me, he said, 'Auntie', he said, 'did you notice what Mr. Pratt did?' I said, 'no, I didn't,' I said. Well, he told up his plate like a - I often think about it - he said,
 'didn't you notice when he took up his plate,' he said, ' and with his dessert spoon took up the juice and cream?' 'No,' I said, 'I didn't. He said, 'he wasn't very well behaved, was he?' \{BLANK\}
 know what children learnt years ago. They'd got a little manners, they knew, didn't they. But it was funny and think about it now. Do you remember that, Bob? Oh, yes, and of course,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4799013\charrsid6102048  her}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  went and told his mother and he said, 'and then you tell us to behave.' He said, 'he ought to have known better than that', he sai
d. Very nice man he was, indeed. Very nice man. But I never forgot that little incident.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Why did you have a cold meal, was it so that you could get ready?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, it was more convenient, and I used to go out to the service in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did they bring their wives with them, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, Oh, no. It would have been too much of a good thing. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4488453\charrsid6102048 
No, he was a very nice man and I only saw - you know it's often interesting, I know I have been a great reader in my time and I wouldn't miss a book, but
 I can't get interested in it now, really - but I saw his death in the paper a little while ago and you know, I felt so sorry for his wife and yet I never knew him. But you do feel like that, don't you, when you've heard about people. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, used to like read
ing, and of course, education's a fine thing, but then our parents couldn't afford it. I don't know if people agree with me - some the children today, they - well, I don't know, they dress well and all that sort of thing, they've certainly got none of the
 manners that - well, some of the children had years ago. I don't say they're all like that, but,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4799013\charrsid6102048  dear}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
 me. You young people, of course, must think we old people are very quaint but, you know, things have changed. Oh, they have changed. And a lot for the bet
ter, oh, yes, I mean, take the old age pensions, well, after all, we know there's nothing to spare, but if people are careful and all that sort of thing, and you take care and have took care, I mean, we've got nothing to complain about.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 You think not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
No, we haven't, no. But of course, it's the younger people, you see, they have a good time, they earn good money and of course, in our time it was wonderful if we could save a little bit, but today they might save, but they just don't, some of them
. I don't say all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
There's a tremendous emphasis in the papers and television and everything, the people to be buying things all the time and I think this is terrible. When you used to entertain the preachers, when did you start that? Was it before the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4799013\charrsid6102048 F}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 irst World War?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Was that before the War, when we first had the preachers, Bob? Well listen, we married 1916 - soon after we married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Soon after you married you started? And the same system was going on all that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Do they still have the system of entertaining?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Well, no, because places like the churches have gone down. Aren't they, the church and things have gone down and we seldom get a man - a minister to come and take the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8405883\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  services. They used to come in the mor
ning and have lunch or dinner or what it was, and then they took another service in the afternoon and then went home. Well, lately it's been morning and evening service, so they go home to their lunch or their dinner, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Could you tell me someth
ing about your reading, when you used to read in the afternoons? What you used to like to read - what kind of books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, well, I don't know. Silly books, sometimes they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 When did you first get interested in reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, I was a good
 reader at school? Yes, we used to - of course, at our schools in our day there was the school books and the teacher would call out the page to find and then she'd call on one to read and then another to read you see. And if we didn't know - we didn't alw
ays know the words, perhaps and she would tell us the word or ask us to spell it out. That's how we }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4488453\charrsid6102048 were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  taught, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did you all have a book?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Books were given out. That was the one blessing, you see. Then another one we'd have an arithmetic
 lesson, and a writing lesson that we used to call 'dictation', now it's composition, isn't it? And the other one would read us a story and - the picture about Rosalie and I suppose you've heard all about Peep Behind the Scenes, of course, and it was a lo
v
ely story for children ... I believe grownups enjoyed it. Well, after I got out to domestic service and it was when I was at the Browns and only getting a very little money I used to look in the bookshop and I saw a book up there, Peep Behind the Scenes. 
'
Oh,' I thought, 'Oh, I would love to buy that book, ' and I knew I couldn't afford it, 'I don't know, perhaps I will one day.' Well, I don't know how long it was after that, and I'm not sure if I saw it in the window again I was out one afternoon, but any
w
ay, I went into the shop. I'm not sure if I saw in the window, and I asked them if they'd got a book, Peep Behind the Scenes. They said 'yes', I asked them how much is it and they said 1/6. Well, to me it seemed a lot, and I bought it and I've got it now 
and think }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4488453\charrsid6102048 a tremendous}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  lot of it. Children galore had that to read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 You mean you lent it to children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Lent it, yes, yes. But they don't want books like that today, do they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Who was the author of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Is there a lady, the name of Watson, or is the name Swan?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 I know the name, I've never read it. And you first got interested 'cos she showed you this lantern slide of it, was that it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes. I can't remember. Do you, Booby? Walton, Mrs. Walton. Have you heard of her at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, I haven't. I've heard of the book, but I haven't heard of her name. When you were a child, after school would you read at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, I read that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8405883\charrsid6102048 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  times, yes. I'll tell you what I used to do. Sometimes when the meal was ready Mother said 'come on, tea
 time.' And perhaps if I was reading, you know, I'd get a book and put it under my chair, She said, 'you can take that book away, you're going to have your tea before you read.' I've gone to the table many a time with a book under my chair. She'd say, 'Yo
u've plenty of time to read that, you put it away.'
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Where did you get books from when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, I don't know, they wouldn't be expensive books. I tell you what, we used to get a prize at the Sunday School every year, a }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4799013\charrsid6102048 b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 ook for a prize and we used to exchange and lend them to each other and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Was there a library?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
There was and I did join once, but it was a job and I didn't properly understand it and I didn't get what I wanted and I thought 'oh, well.' And
 then sometimes in domestic service they said 'if you would like to go and get a book to read you can'. Sometimes you could, you see. There isn't everybody like reading. I like it now, but I .... I tell you what I had given me, in fact I think I've got 8 
of them, I'm not sure. Oh, I've got an old machine cover packed up with books - now, those books.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, yes, I haven't seen those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, they're wonderful. I read them. Of course, they wouldn't appeal to a person like yourself but, I mean, they're r
eally wonderful. They're very nice. They're called The Friendship Book, by Frances Gaye, and this old friend at Clacton, she said - I think I've got 8 now - she sends me one every year for Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Can I have a look at one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 This is '64. That's '68, I think. That's not so good this year, not near so good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Very nice photographs. Do you remember the names of any other books you liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, Annie - is there a book called Annie Swan?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 There may be, I don't know. Mrs. Henry }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4799013\charrsid6102048 W}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 ood, is it by?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And Little Women and Good Wives, and I used to have \{ILLEGIBLE\}
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, I've not read that. I've heard about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 I think Mrs. Henry Wood was the writer of some of those books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did you ever read Uncle Tom's Cabin?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, yes, I've got it, yes, but I'm not quite interested in that. I wasn't no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Why do you think you weren't so interested in that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, I thought it seemed a little bit hard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 You mean the life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, not really, there wasn't a lot of kindness shown through the book, was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No.
