\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Who would you lend them to, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, I lent one, I th
ink, to a poor old chap that's passed away. Then my husband at his work, he used to get talking to different people and he'd talk the book, perhaps, when he talked they said 'have you read those books that are told in there?' and he said, 'Yes, we 've jus
t bought them.' 'I wish you'd lend us one.' Well, he did and he can't get it back, you see. Still, I don't much mind now, I've read them and at my time of life, well, I don't suppose I shall read any more. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 There was Mrs. Henry Wood and there was another author who was very popular.
