And when you used to go to the Sunday School outings in Clacton when you were a child, what sort of vehicle did you go in? What kind of transport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, they used to have a brake, what they call a brake.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. J: A wagonette.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mrs. J: A wagonette, yes, yes.</subject2>
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
And another thing about when you were in domestic service; did you have any celebrations that the employers gave you? Did they ever give a party for the servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Or presents at Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, yes, yes. Presents at Christmas, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 What was it that they gave you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, I remember one year I had a box of chocolates, very pleased with them, when I was at Bromley Hall, half a dozen most lovely han
dkerchiefs with my initial on in a fancy box and I thought it was wonderful. And the house parlour maid, it's a most extraordinary thing, but she gave me a very nice cake plate with a nice plated handle, and I've got it now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did they always give you something, people you worked for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, oh, no, I don't think I - I believe we used to have a little money from another place, I'm not sure. I don't remember other presents.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Just a little money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Money, yes. 5/-. And another thing, if they had
 any visitors come to stay for any length of time and stay such a thing as a week or a fortnight, when they went away they would give us, perhaps, 5/-. Well, we used to take it, you know, as a little extra wage we'd made.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 I was very interested when I talked to an old gentleman once whose wife had been a housemaid in a house where they kept about}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11677498\charrsid6102048  8}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
 different people, you know, servants, and he said at Christmas they used to have a big party and their own dinner, the servants. You never had anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, never had - never, never, no.
