\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mrs. J: Well I think that was the beginning, really speaking, of domest
ic service going down because, you see, they couldn't get them. They got into War work, the girls did, most of them. They got more money.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did you ever think of working after you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, no, I didn't. Well, I - no, I didn't, did I?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. J: No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, I didn't, really, but there was a lady on the back road, on a farm on the back road, the poor old Shields. They were }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8801673\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  very old people and they came from the \{BLANK\} somewhere and they bought that place; and they'd got a da
ughter - daughters. They did live at home. One was a - as a matter fact one was on the Titanic (I don't know what year that was in). Well, are way, I used to go }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8801673\charrsid6102048 2 or 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  mornings a week and help. They didn't have any}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8801673\charrsid6102048 one,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
 she did work herself. They were particularly nice people. Then they sold the place and, of course, went away. Well, I think one of them died there, but otherwise....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 That was after you were married, you used to go and help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 After I was married, yes. They were nice old people, but, 
you know, the wages was very - got very little for going. And then the family - she' got a family of girls, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8801673\charrsid6102048 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  of them, and }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8801673\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
 boys. But the girls always come home for their summer holidays and then she used to get me to go in every day so I could do some co
oking. I went extra then. Otherwise, I didn't - no, I didn't think I ought to get married - go to work after I got married! (laughter) No!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Was that the usual idea then, in those days, that after you got married you didn't go out to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 But did other people think the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, I don't know, there wasn't any went, were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. J: No, not that I knew, they didn't have the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, no, they didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 You mother had to work, of course, doing the butter, didn't she? She had to do that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Because it was a tied cottage, really, wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Well, when we lived in the farm house, you seem Mother used to look after the fowls and if they wanted any killed and they used to be killed, Mother had to pluck
 them and do all like that. Now, Father, I think I told you, worked oh Sundays - not all day - feed what they called the stock, morning, noon at night, so if he wanted to go out he couldn't go out, only in the middle of the day. And that was what it was s
upposed to pay the rent, you see. They called it rent free, but you see, you're paying for that indirectly, aren't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, of course you are, yes. Can you tell me the date of your wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. J: 24}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \super\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  June, 1916.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Now, you mentioned a daym
an on the farm when you first worked there and my husband said I should ask you about him. Why was he called a 'day man'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. J: Well, that's the name that they gave him because he used to do anything on the farm, you see. Well, going back to the tim
e that we drilled the corn, in that time they used to do the fences up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 The daymen, used to, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 The daymen. The stockman - he kept a stockman and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8801673\charrsid6102048 he}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  kept a shepherd, and of course, I was anything, \{BLANK\}. Well, we used to do the fence up, now like, in that time, 'till such a time as he wanted to get the land ready to grow the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4488453\charrsid6102048 mangels}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  and swedes for the stock, what was a coming into the yards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And then after that, was the dayman not needed any more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, well, it was like this. W
e used to go through the summer like that; the beet used to come up, we used to hoe them out, we used to hoe the swedes out and probably we'd hoe them through twice to keep them clean. And then they be grown through the summer and time they were grown we'
d be doing the harvest you see. But mind you, they weren't - we didn't have binders and we didn't have the combines. We straddled the scythe. There was 8 men and a half, and I was the half-man that year, but I had my }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8801673\charrsid6102048 cut}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  with the scythe in cutting the corn.
 And then, when we get - that's after we cut it and that like, that was all tied up, all the corn what we cut it was all tied, we tied it by hand and that was tied up like this, you see, to or to dry into \{BLANK\}
 Well, after we done cutting, we used to start carting and there used to be }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8801673\charrsid6102048 8}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  and a half, there used to be }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8801673\charrsid6102048 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
 in the field with loading the wagons, for at the stockyard unloading, and this lad used to drive wagon from one place to the other, from the field to the stockyard. You understand what I mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, I do. You said there were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8405883\charrsid6102048 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  at the 'something' unloading. What we the word you used?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
What we called the stockyard. Used to be stacked up. All these sheaves, they used to be stacked up, you see. And after it was stacked, there used be a ro
of like that and there used to be a man going round the same as I use to and we used to - I used to have all them stacks thatched, you see. We then, after they were thatched I held the stock in the yards, but I'd pull these }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4488453\charrsid6102048 mangels}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  or beet and these swedes
 off and they'd be stored up for the winter to feed the stocks in the yards, you see. And the - and some of them would be done and they'd be left on the field and they'd be heaped up from the sheep, and there'd be the shepherd to see after them all the wi
nter. That's what I used to do. Of course, at that time of day there used to be what they call thrashing tackles. I used to go from farm to farm and thrash the corn, you see, and everyone didn't have - one used to have a drum for thrashing and}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8801673\charrsid6102048  mother}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  used to have the pitcher to put the straw up and that, like, and of course, that time, well, I wanted such a thing as }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8801673\charrsid6102048 7 or 8}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
 men. Well, them what are on the farm, they'd perhaps have a man buy some to thrash it and then they'd be vice versa, he'd lend his men fo
r that man to do it. That's how they used to go. And sometimes, well, at that time of day there several people hadn't got a job to do. Well, they were there, when that machine was there, they were there after a job, just doing what was there. See, that's 
how that was.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And then how long would those people, who were normally unemployed, have that job? How long did the thrashing tackle go out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, it wouldn't be above a day or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8801673\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  there. After he'd been a day or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8801673\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048  he'd got off somewhere else to another farm for a day or }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8801673\charrsid6102048 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 . That's how they went about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And he'd be paid by the day, would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, he'd be paid by the day. Yes, yes, he'd be paid by the day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 So there'd be some people who never had a permanent job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, there would be
 some. If they were lucky enough they might get a permanent job - and they might not, you see. Things were very much harden then to what they are now. Very much harder.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And the dayman, was he laid off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, no. No, he was never laid off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 His terms of employment were the same as the rest of you, were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, them what was working on the farm, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 I see, so it was just his name, it didn't refer to his terms of employment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, no, no, no, no. They used to practically do anything. That's what he used to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
If the farmer - you know, the old gentleman you did work for first - did want to get rid of a man, did he have to give him a month's notice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 A week. That's a week either way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Do you remember that happening to anybody, this giving of notice to anyone?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 No, I don't. No, I don't remember it at all, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 If a man did lose his job with a farmer in those days, would he have difficulty getting another job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Well, he might do, but if a man change his j
ob he go from one farm to another and according to what he was, the man what he was a going to, he wouldn't take him away. He wouldn't take him away from that man, you see. That's how that was then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And my husband also said to ask you did your mother,
 when she cooked, cook on an open fire? What sort of a range or cooking fire did she have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 An open fire, open at the side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And so if she fried something, that would be on the coals, would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, yes. She never had no oil stove or anything. We only had that one fire, like, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 I didn't ask your wife this, but was her mother the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Yes, yes, oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And you said you used to play music in other people's houses, who were the people whose houses you used to go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Well, I had a brother; and my wife's brother. Oh, we used to go back and forth to one another, and perhaps we'd be friendly with someone else and we' go to his, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And would they come and play at your house, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Your wife's brother played, did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Yes, yes, used to play one like that, one like mine. My brother played one like that, he'd play a violin and the last thing he played, he played a corn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4991773\charrsid6102048 et}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Did other families in the village, also in Ardleigh, play instruments.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 They were quite common, were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, yes, yes, yes, quite common.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Was it usually wind instruments that they played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Wind or violin, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And the family that came for a meal on Sundays, who were they? Were they the preachers, or were they friends?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
No, they were friends. Probably - we used to have meetings over here in the open air, what we used to call camp meetings. There'd be other people come with instruments and they'd pl
ay with us and we'd take them in, have that in like, with us for dinner, so they'd start again in the afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Oh, I see. They'd come over and play and then they'd come home for a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 They'd come here and have their dinner and then they'd go back and start again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Where would they come from in the first place, those people?
