\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. J: No, there wasn't, no. No, not then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 But did she take an interest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16072274 AJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 Mr. J: Oh, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 And your mother, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3289702 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14893121\charrsid6102048 
Mrs. J: Oh, yes, she took an interest, but of course, she didn't vote, you know. My brothers were, and especially my youngest brother, my sister-in-law's husband, h
e didn't get a vote but he was absolutely crazy wanting it. He wouldn't miss a meeting, he'd go to all the meetings and if he wanted to them a question, if it was ridiculous he'd ask it and he got an answer, and was full of it, wasn't he, Bob? And I used 
t
o say to my husband, I used to say, 'Oh, I hope he don't come here tonight.' Perhaps at election time somebody'd come in, there'd be an argument. They didn't get cross with each other, but it was all the time politics, politics, politics, you got fed up w
ith it. But the young people are not so interested in it to-day, no. I don't think so.</subject2>
